The paper deals with the performance of Spatially-Coupled LDPC (SC-LDPC) ensembles on binary erasure channels affected by bursts, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The burst erasure model is also relevant to networked systems (cs.NI) and distributed storage (cs.DS). The paper discusses the effect of increasing the variable node degree and expurgating the ensemble, which are topics related to coding theory (cs.SI) and complexity theory (cs.CC).
